body:
Expected: trying to send values of an incorrect type should be an error at the `send` call.

When compiling code that tries to send a values of a non-Sized type, an error is reported on the type's definition: [playpen](http://is.gd/6kdX1j)

``` rust
use std::error::Error;
use std::io;
use std::thread;
use std::sync::mpsc::channel;
use std::sync::Arc;

#[derive(Debug)]
struct A { // Error reported here
    b: Arc<Error>
}

fn main() {
    // Create a simple streaming channel
    let (tx, rx) = channel();
    let t = thread::scoped(move|| {
        tx.send(A{ b: Arc::new(io::Error::new(io::ErrorKind::Other, "other", None)) }).unwrap();
    });
    t.join();
    let v = rx.recv().unwrap();
    println!("{:?}",v);
}
```

When compiling code that tries to send a values of a non-Send type, an error is reported on the `channel()` call site: [playpen](http://is.gd/p85Gij)

``` rust
use std::boxed::Box;
use std::error::Error;
use std::io;
use std::thread;
use std::sync::mpsc::channel;

#[derive(Debug)]
struct A {
    b: Box<Error>
}

fn main() {
    // Create a simple streaming channel
    let (tx, rx) = channel(); // Error reported here
    let t = thread::scoped(move|| {
        tx.send(A{ b: Box::new(io::Error::new(io::ErrorKind::Other, "other", None)) }).unwrap();
    });
    t.join();
    let v = rx.recv().unwrap();
    println!("{:?}",v);
}
```
